The paper deals with domain adaptation in computer vision, which is a problem typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) communities. Finally, the experiments involve tasks such as digit classification and object recognition, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
